<div id="review_1393874235" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1393874235" />
    <a title="Sally Hirschwek" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/46791773-sally-hirschwek"><img alt="Sally Hirschwek" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1393874235?book_show_action=true">Sep 16, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sally Hirschwek" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sally Hirschwek" href="/user/show/46791773-sally-hirschwek">Sally Hirschwek</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1393874235" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15130628341957775609">I thought this book was amazing! It captured this incredible mind of young, remarkable girl living in the mid nineteen hundreds Davita Chandal. It captured her struggle to accept the world and it&apos;s injustices. The world she came to realize, was not a fair place sometimes. She learned you can not deny it, or pretend it doesn&apos;t exist. You must do what you can to seek the bad in the world. It has to be clear to you though, that you can not solve all of the worlds problems. They will never be fully </span>
  <span id="freeText15130628341957775609" style="display:none">I thought this book was amazing! It captured this incredible mind of young, remarkable girl living in the mid nineteen hundreds Davita Chandal. It captured her struggle to accept the world and it's injustices. The world she came to realize, was not a fair place sometimes. She learned you can not deny it, or pretend it doesn't exist. You must do what you can to seek the bad in the world. It has to be clear to you though, that you can not solve all of the worlds problems. They will never be fully solved. Davita learned that you must live through the struggles of the real life, face it's truth, and continue moving on. She learned your imagination can come in handy to. Never give up hope through all of this. Everyone has a place in the world, and it is up to you to find it. The finding of who you are is not a short process, and it may change. It is called the journey of life, and everyone must take it. Through imagination, stories, struggle, perseverance, love, and thought, Davita learned these lessons. She is an inspirational young lady. This book, like the other Potok novel I read, will continue to stick with me, and I will constantly be pondering their meaning of the book, and follow to follow it, knowing there may be more than one. I would definitely recommend this book to anyone who loves deep thought and meaning.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15130628341957775609" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
